A police commander confirmed that a child was among those killed in the accident which left three police officers seriously injured. JOHANNESBURG â€“ At least 14 people have been killed and others seriously injured after a police truck rolled over in Baringo county in west Kenya. Police have confirmed the accident saying the truck was carrying officers and residents who had gone shopping. Authorities say the driver lost control of the vehicle and it veered off the road. There were five police officers on board and an unknown number of civilians. A police commander confirmed that a child was among those killed in the accident which left three police officers seriously injured.